Here's the corrected PlantUML component diagram for the sup2is_e-commerce-project deployment architecture:

```plantuml
@startuml sup2is_e-commerce-project

skinparam componentStyle uml2
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam nodesep 20
skinparam ranksep 30

rectangle "Client Layer" as clients {
  component "Web Browser" as browser
  component "Mobile App" as mobile
}

rectangle "API Gateway" as gateway {
  component "Zuul Proxy" as zuul
  component "JWT Filter" as jwtfilter
}

rectangle "Service Discovery" as eureka <<Eureka Server>> 

rectangle "Microservices" as services {
  component "Member Service" as member <<Spring Boot>> 
  component "Order Service" as order <<Spring Boot>> 
  component "Product Service" as product <<Spring Boot>> 
  component "Auth Service" as auth <<Spring Boot>> 
}

rectangle "Data Layer" as datastores {
  component "MySQL" as mysql <<RDS>> 
  component "Redis" as redis <<ElastiCache>> 
  component "Kafka" as kafka <<Message Queue>> 
}

rectangle "Support Services" as support {
  component "Config Server" as config <<Spring Config>> 
  component "Zipkin" as zipkin <<Tracing>> 
}

' Connections
browser --> gateway : HTTP/HTTPS
mobile --> gateway

gateway --> eureka : Service lookup
jwtfilter --> auth : Token validation

member --> eureka : Register
order --> eureka : Register
product --> eureka : Register
auth --> eureka : Register

member --> mysql : JPA
order --> mysql : JPA
product --> mysql : JPA
auth --> mysql : JPA

member --> redis : Cache
product --> redis : Cache

product --> kafka : Publish events
order --> kafka : Consume events

order --> product : Feign Client

member --> config : Get config
order --> config : Get config
product --> config : Get config
auth --> config : Get config

member --> zipkin : Tracing
order --> zipkin : Tracing
product --> zipkin : Tracing
auth --> zipkin : Tracing

@enduml
```